<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-652-298  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 652 298.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  July 2 1990 v219 n1 p9(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MFS seeks ruling on RHC fiber rings. (Metropolitan Fiber Systems,Bell regional holding companies) (News of the Week)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mason, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Metropolitan Fiber Systems has requested that state and federalregulatory agencies check into the local fiber optic network plansof five of the Bell regional holding companies and prevent thosecarriers from using residential and small business subscribersubsidies to fund the construction of the fiber optic networks,which will mainly be used to sell advanced information services tolarge business customers.andP;  The FCC tends to support the activitiesof the telephone companies, which claim that they are onlyattempting to 'modernize' their services instead of effectuallyentering into a new market.andP;  US West, Southwestern Bell, Nynex,Pacific Telesis and Ameritech are the companies in question.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Telephone companiesBell Regional Holding CompaniesFiber opticsCompetitionUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionInformation servicesTelecommunications Services.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>